00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:36,530
Anyway, the Gintaman's serialization
is already in its fifth week,

226
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:39,590
so we can't suddenly change the
visual look of the main character

227
00:11:39,590 --> 00:11:42,020
to something completely
different now, anyway.

228
00:11:42,020 --> 00:11:44,580
You know, you can say his perm failed.

229
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:46,610
Or he had a perm explosion... Boom!

230
00:11:46,610 --> 00:11:47,310
Uho!

231
00:11:47,310 --> 00:11:49,540
Why does it look like you're
saying, "I'll take that idea!"

232
00:11:49,540 --> 00:11:52,090
We already had something
ridiculous like that before!

233
00:11:52,260 --> 00:11:55,140
All right, we finished the main character,
so next we'll talk about the enemy!

234
00:11:55,140 --> 00:11:57,230
Hey! You're pursuing this
subject all by yourself!

235
00:11:57,790 --> 00:12:02,350
Listen! In order for the main character
to stand out, a strong rival is needed.

236
00:12:02,350 --> 00:12:07,100
[Note: Parody of Shichibukia and The Seven Warlords of the sea from One Piece and Bankai from Bleach and the Akatsuki from Naruto.]

237
00:12:02,350 --> 00:12:07,100
Right... Like One Park's Chichibukai.
Or Belt's "Bakazuki."

238
00:12:03,370 --> 00:12:05,440
[CHICHIBUKAI]

239
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:07,540
[BAKAZUKI]

240
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:11,710
The main character beats his strongest
enemy, so it makes him cool.

241
00:12:11,870 --> 00:12:15,140
And sometimes a strong enemy
winds up becoming a friend,

242
00:12:15,140 --> 00:12:16,500
so he becomes more exciting.

243
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:17,450
Hmm...

244
00:12:17,450 --> 00:12:20,830
So, Gintaman's rival character is...

245
00:12:20,830 --> 00:12:23,290
This guy? Who's this, anyway?!

246
00:12:23,290 --> 00:12:25,460
It's a detective from the Shinjuku
police station, Dorokata-san.

247
00:12:23,290 --> 00:12:25,460
[Note: Parody of Hijikata.]

248
00:12:25,460 --> 00:12:32,200
[DOROKATA]

249
00:12:25,460 --> 00:12:29,540
Sometimes he hunts down Ginta-san
and sometimes he helps him.

250
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:32,200
It's a character that screams, "closest
rival" but is really a "friend."

251
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:38,850
I already told you that it's too plain! Can
you identify him by his silhouette?

252
00:12:38,850 --> 00:12:40,400
Don't make me repeat the same
thing so many times.

253
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,760
Are you guys stupid or something?

254
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:45,190
Look at these. In JUMP, these are the
silhouettes of the rival characters.

255
00:12:45,190 --> 00:12:47,670
See, no one looks the same.

256
00:12:47,670 --> 00:12:49,640
So you do know all about it, right?

257
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,500
You know about Dragon Bozu, right?

258
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:54,970
Well, it's not my fault if the top people
come complaining to us.

259
00:12:54,970 --> 00:12:57,050
Shut up and die.

260
00:12:57,050 --> 00:12:59,500
I'm sure the top people will be able
to handle it, so don't worry.

261
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:00,410
Nothing to worry about.

262
00:13:00,410 --> 00:13:01,220
I doubt it!

263
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:04,010
More importantly, look
carefully, right here.

264
00:13:04,010 --> 00:13:05,560
Well, do you recognize who this is?

265
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:07,300
Um... Pickle-san.

266
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:07,300
[Note: Parody of Piccolo from Dragon Ball.]

267
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:08,450
Then, how about this?

268
00:13:08,450 --> 00:13:11,100
[Note: Parody of Tien Shinhan from Dragon Ball.]

269
00:13:08,450 --> 00:13:11,100
That shiny head belongs
to Tenshindon-san.

270
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:12,550
And this?

271
00:13:12,550 --> 00:13:13,700
Oh, Bajita.

272
00:13:12,550 --> 00:13:13,700
[Note: Parody of Vegeta from Dragon Ball.]

273
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:15,650
Bu bu. That's wrong.

274
00:13:15,650 --> 00:13:18,310
What! Don't tell me... This
time, the rival character...!

275
00:13:18,310 --> 00:13:19,830
The answer is...

276
00:13:19,830 --> 00:13:21,430
...it's Ginta-san.

277
00:13:21,430 --> 00:13:25,020
To be precise, it's Ginta-san after
he turns into a Super Yasain.

278
00:13:21,430 --> 00:13:25,020
[Note: Parody of Super Saiyan from Dragon Ball.]

279
00:13:25,020 --> 00:13:26,840
Why?! Why is Ginta-san here again?!

280
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:28,420
Why are you asking such
tricky questions?!

281
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:30,490
What was the point of talking
about rival characters?!

282
00:13:30,490 --> 00:13:33,120
And why did he turn into
a Super Yasain?!

283
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:35,390
Why is he steadily getting stronger?!

284
00:13:37,390 --> 00:13:38,200
Uho

285
00:13:37,540 --> 00:13:43,400
[Ginta-san.]

286
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,010
Why did you answer such
a tricky question?!

287
00:13:40,010 --> 00:13:43,400
Stop smiling! This isn't a quiz!

288
00:13:43,420 --> 00:13:48,950
So, this rival character appears as an enemy
at first, but ends up being a friend.

289
00:13:48,950 --> 00:13:50,950
That's the real thrill of a boy's manga.

290
00:13:50,950 --> 00:13:54,280
Then what's the meaning
of this discussion?!

291
00:13:54,470 --> 00:13:57,850
Well, it's something like this: He
fights with his rival and wins.

292
00:13:57,850 --> 00:13:59,680
Then they become friends
without knowing it.

293
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:02,840
And a new rival appears, and
he fights and wins again.

294
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:04,530
And he makes a new friend.

295
00:14:04,530 --> 00:14:08,050
Repeating this and dragging it on
is the standard JUMP formula.

296
00:14:08,050 --> 00:14:11,800
[Note: Parody of Yamcha from Dragon Ball.]

297
00:14:08,050 --> 00:14:11,800
Hey! One person is missing! Namcha?!
Is that Namcha?

298
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:14,450
Well, that's what the
rival part is all about.

299
00:14:14,450 --> 00:14:18,550
Hey! Let him in! Let Namcha
join in the JUMP formula!

300
00:14:18,550 --> 00:14:21,510
The next thing is... Let's talk
about the comedy part.

301
00:14:21,510 --> 00:14:23,010
Namcha!

302
00:14:23,690 --> 00:14:28,750
Well, as far as appearances go, "Gintaman"
is more like a comedy manga...

303
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:33,620
...but as you know, a gag is created
by a funny man and a straight man.

304
00:14:33,620 --> 00:14:38,030
There're some gags where there's only a funny
man and no straight man at all, but...

305
00:14:38,790 --> 00:14:41,750
If that's the case, the reader can be
the straight man while he reads.

306
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:45,170
Wherever there's laughter,
there's a straight man.

307
00:14:45,170 --> 00:14:48,150
Now you guys understand how important
it is to have a straight man, don't you?

308
00:14:48,150 --> 00:14:49,100
Uhoho!

309
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:50,830
However...

310
00:14:50,830 --> 00:14:55,010
...in Gintaman's case, I can see that
this straight man went slightly too far.

311
00:14:56,410 --> 00:14:57,960
Please take a look at this.

312
00:14:58,390 --> 00:14:59,150
Huh?

313
00:14:58,390 --> 00:14:59,150
Uho?

314
00:14:59,380 --> 00:15:01,380
[REWIND]

315
00:15:00,940 --> 00:15:01,420
Watch.

316
00:15:01,380 --> 00:15:02,680
[PLAY]

317
00:15:01,420 --> 00:15:03,290
Why?! Why is Ginta-san here again?!

318
00:15:03,290 --> 00:15:04,880
Why are you asking such
tricky questions?!

319
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:07,190
What was the point of talking
about rival characters?!

320
00:15:07,190 --> 00:15:09,450
And why did he turn into
a Super Yasain?!

321
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:12,350
Why is he steadily getting stronger?!

322
00:15:12,350 --> 00:15:16,240
All right. As you can see, this straight
man is obviously overdoing it.

323
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:19,230
This isn't manga. It's what I said earlier!

324
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:24,800
A straight man's role is to explain the funny
man's joke so that people understand, but...

325
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:25,250
Watch.

326
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:26,000
Why?!

327
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,110
Why is Ginta-san here again?!

328
00:15:27,110 --> 00:15:28,730
Why are you asking such
tricky questions?!

329
00:15:28,730 --> 00:15:30,930
What was the point of talking
about rival characters?!

330
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:33,190
And why did he turn into
a Super Yasain?!

331
00:15:33,190 --> 00:15:35,510
Why is he steadily getting stronger?!

332
00:15:36,050 --> 00:15:40,030
If he nitpicks about every little thing
like this, people will get bored.

333
00:15:40,030 --> 00:15:40,530
Watch.

334
00:15:40,380 --> 00:15:40,750
["WHY" 0 times]

335
00:15:40,530 --> 00:15:42,420
Why?! Why is Ginta-san here again?!

336
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:41,520
["WHY" 1 time]

337
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:46,820
["WHY" 2 times]

338
00:15:42,420 --> 00:15:44,000
Why are you asking such
tricky questions?!

339
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,180
What was the point of talking
about rival characters?!

340
00:15:46,180 --> 00:15:48,630
And why did he turn into
a Super Yasain?!

341
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:48,890
["WHY" 3 times]

342
00:15:48,630 --> 00:15:50,760
Why is he steadily getting stronger?!

343
00:15:48,890 --> 00:15:50,760
["WHY" 4 times]

344
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:54,170
See? You said "WHY?"
four times in one cut.

345
00:15:54,170 --> 00:15:57,490
Stop! I'm so embarrassed,
so please stop it!

346
00:15:57,490 --> 00:16:01,250
When the straight man is played in a
subtle manner, it's far more effective.

347
00:16:01,250 --> 00:16:07,030
It encourages the reader to actually think about
the joke and the straight man's explanation.

348
00:16:07,030 --> 00:16:13,520
It helps suck the reader in. But when
you try to explain everything...

349
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:14,360
Watch.

350
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:16,250
Why?! Why is Ginta-san here again?!

351
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:17,910
Why are you asking such
tricky questions?!

352
00:16:17,910 --> 00:16:20,060
What was the point of talking
about rival characters?!

353
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:22,290
And why did he turn into
a Super Yasain?!

354
00:16:22,290 --> 00:16:24,760
Why is he steadily getting stronger?!

355
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:28,130
You've obviously lost your
effectiveness as a straight man

356
00:16:28,130 --> 00:16:30,020
and have become plain
annoying instead...

357
00:16:30,020 --> 00:16:35,600
Stop! Fine! Kill me! Everything
will be all right if I die!

358
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:40,090
In other words, the straight man's
job isn't to just explain something.

359
00:16:40,090 --> 00:16:43,510
Aren't you just pointing out my faults?

360
00:16:43,510 --> 00:16:45,380
Anyway, that's about it.

361
00:16:45,380 --> 00:16:50,140
I have someone who is the top straight man
in Edo, so you'd better learn from him.

362
00:16:50,140 --> 00:16:51,530
Let me introduce him to you.

363
00:16:52,010 --> 00:16:53,360
This is Ginta-san.

364
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:55,480
Dondake!

365
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:58,850
[Note: "Dondake" is a popular catch phrase used by gay people in Japan. Literally means "WTF?!" Similar to American gay people who snap their fingers and say "Oh no you didn't!"]

366
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:58,850
It's something like that.
I invented that phrase recently.

367
00:16:58,850 --> 00:17:00,590
It can cover almost all
funny-man situations.

368
00:17:00,590 --> 00:17:02,030
Dondake!

369
00:17:02,030 --> 00:17:05,200
If you keep using that word most
of the time, it'll be all right.

370
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:06,970
What kind of comedy is that?!

371
00:17:06,970 --> 00:17:07,760
No, no.

372
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:08,780
Dondake!

373
00:17:08,780 --> 00:17:09,740
D-Dondake!

374
00:17:09,740 --> 00:17:10,140
One more time.

375
00:17:10,140 --> 00:17:10,780
Dondake!

376
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:11,770
Dondake!

377
00:17:11,770 --> 00:17:12,230
Say it once more!

378
00:17:12,230 --> 00:17:13,050
Dondake!

379
00:17:13,050 --> 00:17:13,880
Dondake!

380
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:14,530
Everybody say it!

381
00:17:14,530 --> 00:17:15,310
Dondake!

382
00:17:15,310 --> 00:17:16,360
Dondake!

383
00:17:16,360 --> 00:17:16,950
Everybody say it!

384
00:17:16,950 --> 00:17:17,670
Dondake!

385
00:17:17,670 --> 00:17:19,940
Dondake!

386
00:17:23,450 --> 00:17:26,870
And this year's top buzzword is...

387
00:17:28,620 --> 00:17:31,740
"Dondake!"

388
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:35,700
Everybody, "Dondake!"

389
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:46,440
[This year's buzzword award!]

390
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:46,440
[Shonen JUMP Editorial Department
Kohei Konishi]

391
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:46,440
[LIVE]

392
00:17:37,370 --> 00:17:40,150
Here we have Kohei Konishi-san
who created "Dondake!"

393
00:17:40,150 --> 00:17:44,710
He is from the weekly Shonen
JUMP editorial department.

394
00:17:44,710 --> 00:17:46,670
Please tell us how you feel right now.

395
00:17:46,670 --> 00:17:50,490
Well, it's not like I wanted to
launch a new catchy trend...

396
00:17:50,490 --> 00:17:52,890
I just worked hard and it
came about naturally.

397
00:17:52,890 --> 00:17:57,950
So I don't know what to say.

398
00:17:58,120 --> 00:18:01,250
But...I have just one thing
to say to young people.

399
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:05,710
If you have something that you really think
is fun, think about it and pursue it.

400
00:18:06,140 --> 00:18:09,900
After all, that's the shortcut
to success, I think.

401
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:12,640
[Meet a deadline! By Konishi.]

402
00:18:10,970 --> 00:18:11,870
Uho.

403
00:18:12,860 --> 00:18:17,740
Whatever... No one can overcome
someone who loves his work.

404
00:18:18,450 --> 00:18:20,540
Tsk... I lost...

405
00:18:20,540 --> 00:18:21,920
Humph!

406
00:18:26,190 --> 00:18:28,490
I look forward to seeing
you at this new level.

407
00:18:28,490 --> 00:18:29,490
Konishi.

408
00:18:29,490 --> 00:18:34,090
Lastly, I'd like to say one word to all my friends
who taught me something important.

409
00:18:34,090 --> 00:18:36,150
Dondake!

410
00:18:44,930 --> 00:18:47,410
[Note: On JUMP cover, "Gintaman
becomes TV Anime!']

411
00:18:44,930 --> 00:18:47,410
It's still so boring...

412
00:18:48,420 --> 00:18:51,370
I hope Gintaman ends soon.

